article_title: After-hours buzz: CSX, Intel, Phillips 66 & more
article_text: Check out which companies are making headlines after the bell  Tuesday:  CSX - The railway gained in after-hours trading  after posting third-quarter profit that exceeded estimates.  Rival Union Pacific also rose in after-hours  trading.   Intel - The technology giant rose in extended trading after reporting third-quarter revenue that beat  expectations.  Johnson & Johnson - The supplier of  health care products gained in after-hours trading after falling  during the day as investors fretted about competition for hits  hepatitis C treatment.
